# Atelier

A Cowork-style **desktop AI workspace**: a **Go** host service drives a Linux utility VM on
Windows HCS, a **TypeScript** agent loop runs the AI *inside* that VM, and an **Electron/React**
app is the UI. The whole point is letting an AI agent work on **local files** safely — by
containment (the VM is the cage), not per-click consent.

> Full design, decisions, and a glossary live in **[`docs/design.md`](docs/design.md)**; the
> slice-by-slice implementation history and current milestone status live in
> **[`docs/implementation-status.md`](docs/implementation-status.md)**.
> Per-directory build/run/test detail and conventions live in **[`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md)**.

## Status

The whole stack is wired end-to-end: our own Go bindings to Windows HCS boot our own Linux VM, the
host drives the guest over hvsocket, the agent loop runs **inside** the VM (Topology B), and the
Electron app drives it all. Work follows the milestone ladder in
[`docs/implementation-status.md`](docs/implementation-status.md).

- **Host service** (`services`) — a Go broker speaking JSON-RPC 2.0 (Content-Length framed) over a
  named pipe (Windows) / unix socket (dev). Every capability passes a policy gate + audit log.
  - **Boot** — our `computecore.dll` bindings author the compute-system doc and start the VM on a
    self-built, version-matched **kernel + initrd + Ubuntu 22.04 rootfs** bundle.
  - **Compute door** — `exec` runs a command in the guest over hvsocket and streams stdout/stderr
    back live; `execInput` pushes stdin into a long-lived guest process (the persistent agent loop).
  - **Files door** — host folders mount over **9p** on a *running* VM (no reboot). A legacy single
    `/workspace`, plus **concurrent per-session shares** at `/sessions/<id>` (one VM, many folders);
    `readFile`/`writeFile` are broker-mediated and jailed (reject `..` and escaping symlinks).
  - **Network door** — a no-NIC user-mode network (gvisor-tap-vsock) with a default-deny egress
    allowlist + pinning DNS resolver; `setEgressPolicy` swaps the allowlist at runtime. Verified
    live through `vmctl`; the remaining live gate is the desktop UI E2E run.
- **Agent loop** (`packages/agent`) — the Claude Agent SDK loop, running **in the guest**
  (`cli-guest.ts`): one-shot (`vmctl agent`) or a persistent multi-turn `--serve` loop driven over
  stdin/stdout NDJSON. The policy gate (`canUseTool`) audits every tool call; tools act on the guest
  filesystem and only the model call leaves the cage via the egress allowlist.
- **Desktop shell** (`apps/desktop`) — a hardened Electron + React 19 + Tailwind v4 app. **WORK
  mode now drives the real in-guest agent over the broker**: one shared VM hosting **concurrent
  persistent per-session loops**, each with its own folder mount and conversation, with
  **hibernate/resume** to bound guest memory. Chat mode stays mock. The remaining gate is a live
  end-to-end UI run (S6.1); a no-UAC service + MSIX packaging follow (S6.2).

## Build & run the whole stack

### Prerequisites

| For | Need |
|---|---|
| Real VM (boot / exec / files / net) | **Windows 11 + HCS** — Hyper-V Administrators membership *or* run the broker elevated |
| Image-bundle build | **WSL2 + Docker** (plus `mke2fs`, `qemu-img`) — `image/build.sh` is bash |
| Host broker + guest daemon | **Go 1.25+** (toolchain pinned in `services/go.mod`) |
| Desktop app, agent, codegen | **Node ≥ 22.12** |
| The model call | **`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`** in the environment that launches the desktop app (or `vmctl agent`) |

### 1. Build

```sh
# 1a. Build the Go host broker + dev CLI (also regenerates the TS + Go protocol bindings).
.\scripts\build-go.ps1                            # -> services\bin\{host,vmctl}.exe

# 1b. Build the VM image bundle in WSL — cross-compiles guestd + bakes the in-guest agent
#     into the rootfs (needs the protocol bindings from 1a).
(cd image && ./build.sh check && ./build.sh all)  # Windows bundle -> image/bundle/windows-amd64-hyperv/{vmlinuz,initrd,rootfs.vhd}
# macOS (Apple Silicon): make -C image darwin     # arm64 bundle  -> image/bundle/darwin-arm64-vz/{vmlinuz,initrd,rootfs.raw}

# 1c. Install desktop deps (agent deps are baked into the rootfs by build.sh).
npm --prefix apps/desktop install
```

Verify everything compiles/tests with `go build ./... && go test ./...` (in `services`) and
`npm --prefix apps/desktop run typecheck && npm --prefix apps/desktop test` — see [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md).

### 2. Run the full stack (Windows)

```sh
# 2a. Start the host broker — elevated; listens on \\.\pipe\atelier-host.
services\bin\host                      # or, without a build step: go run ./cmd/host

# 2b. Launch the desktop app in a separate shell that inherits ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
npm --prefix apps/desktop start        # or, from the repo root: npm run dev
```

In the app: **Work → New work → pick a folder.** The app ensures `vm0` (`createVM` from the bundle +
`startVM`), mounts the folder at `/sessions/<id>`, opens egress to `api.anthropic.com`, and launches
the in-guest agent loop. Type a task in the composer; assistant text plus tool-call and
policy-decision cards stream in, and deliverables land in your folder. Idle sessions hibernate and
resume on selection.

Desktop env knobs: `ATELIER_BUNDLE_DIR` (point at a per-target bundle dir, e.g. `image\bundle\windows-amd64-hyperv`; the platform-aware default resolver lands in S3), `ATELIER_IDLE_MS` (hibernate after
idle, default 10 min), `ATELIER_MAX_ACTIVE` (live loops before LRU hibernate, default 3),
`ATELIER_BOOT_TIMEOUT_MS` (boot wait, default 120 000).

### 3. Or drive it from a terminal — `vmctl` (no Electron)

Once the broker is up, the built `services\bin\vmctl` (add `services\bin` to `PATH`, or use the full
path) exercises the whole substrate from a shell:

```sh
vmctl createVM -id vm0 -kernel image/bundle/windows-amd64-hyperv/vmlinuz -initrd image/bundle/windows-amd64-hyperv/initrd -rootfs image/bundle/windows-amd64-hyperv/rootfs.vhd
vmctl startVM  -id vm0
vmctl exec     -id vm0 -- python3 --version                  # run in the guest, stream output back
vmctl attachWorkspace -id vm0 -path C:\work\folder           # share a host folder at /workspace
vmctl setEgressPolicy -allow api.anthropic.com
vmctl agent    -id vm0 -- "read orders.csv, write summary.csv"   # run the in-guest agent loop
vmctl stopVM   -id vm0
```

### Dev without HCS (protocol-level, unix socket)

The broker and `vmctl` also run on Linux over a unix socket — no VM — to exercise the Hop-2 protocol:

```sh
cd services
go run ./cmd/host  -addr /tmp/atelier-host.sock &
go run ./cmd/vmctl -addr /tmp/atelier-host.sock getStatus
```

Per-package dev/test/lint commands and conventions are in **[`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md)**.

## Layout

| Dir | What |
|---|---|
| `apps/desktop` | Electron/React desktop UI (chat-forward shell; WORK mode wired to the broker) |
| `services` | Go module — privileged host broker, in-VM daemon (`guestd`), dev CLI (`vmctl`) |
| `packages` | Shared TS libs — agent loop, protocol, provider seam |
| `image` | VM image build pipeline — kernel + initrd + rootfs bundle |
| `tools/protogen` | Protocol codegen — schema → TS + Go |
| `docs` | Design, runtime architecture, implementation, and security docs |

## Architecture at a glance

```
Renderer (React, sandboxed)
   │  Hop 1: Electron IPC
Main process (Node) ── conductor + Session Manager (per-session lifecycle, hibernate/resume)
   │  Hop 2: named pipe / unix socket — JSON-RPC 2.0 (Content-Length)
Go host service ── broker (policy + audit) + HCS driver  ·  privileged
   │  Hop 3: hvsocket — control / exec / files / net planes
Linux utility VM ── one cage, N sessions: each /sessions/<id> mount + its own agent loop (Claude Agent SDK)
   ·  tools act on the guest fs; only the model call exits, via the egress allowlist
```

> Versions: this scaffold uses latest-stable libraries, which diverges from the design doc's
> Cowork version pins (§11). See `AGENTS.md`.
